{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b388e924-8a34-4a30-a133-cf6a58cd7f14","content":"There's no existing pipeline here, so here's a general migration guide.\n\n## Migrating from `VSTest@3` to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n### 1. Update your test projects\n\nAdd/update these NuGet packages in each test `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.7.0\" />\n<!-- TRX report output -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" Version=\"1.6.2\" />\n<!-- Code coverage -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"17.13.2\" />\n```\n\nEnable the new test platform in a `Directory.Build.props` (or per-project):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### 2. Replace `VSTest@3` in your pipeline\n\n**Before:**\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**\\*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)\\TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\n**After:**\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration $(BuildConfiguration)\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --\n      --report-trx\n      --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/coverage.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key differences\n\n| Concern | Old (VSTest@3) | New (Testing Platform) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | `vstest.console.exe` | Built into test binary via `dotnet test` |\n| TRX reports | Built-in | `--report-trx` flag (needs TrxReport package) |\n| Code coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` | `--coverage` flag (needs CodeCoverage package) |\n| Results publish | Automatic | Explicit `PublishTestResults@2` + `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2` |\n\nThe `condition: always()` ensures results are published even when tests fail.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ba56953f-e12a-48fb-94e1-867456c1132c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. This is a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure Pipelines. Let me provide a comprehensive answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":756,"requestId":"681A:3AE99C:7BE507:830AE6:6A044D57"},"id":"cde41328-c499-47c3-ac01-f0b2cd3a4171","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:07:36.525Z","parentId":"c9979174-38b9-4da7-919e-6f4f0b945dbd"}
